{"word":"G96 - ἀδόκιμος - adókimos - ad-ok'-ee-mos - Castaway","slug":"G96","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἀδόκιμος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>adókimos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ad-ok'-ee-mos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Castaway"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B1;&#x0313;&#x03B4;&#x03BF;&#x0301;&#x03BA;&#x03B9;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - adokimos</b> - <i>ad-ok'-ee-mos</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G1\">G1</a> (as a negative particle) and <a href=\"#/G1384\">G1384</a>; <i>unapproved</i>, that is, <i>rejected</i>; by implication <i>worthless</i> (literally or morally): - castaway, rejected, reprobate."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G1381\">G1381</a>, <a href=\"#/G1382\">G1382</a>, <a href=\"#/G1383\">G1383</a>, <a href=\"#/G1384\">G1384</a>"}]}